              "coded_information": [
                "FISCT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-233",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99702
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The   U-233  sample  contained",
                " 52.4 mg deposited in the form of (U-3)(O-8) on  four",
                " titanum  disks each with an active diameter of 40 mm",
                " was used:",
                "     Masses       Isotope     Isotopic percentage",
                "      (MG)           A             (ATOMS/%)",
                "       13.9         233              99.702",
                "       13.          234               0.236",
                "       12.8         235               0.012",
                "       12.7         238               0.05"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The direct  measurements   of   number   of   fission",
                " fragments  using the scanning of the Makrofol sheets",
                " by means of conventional optical microscopy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The  total  errors  are  given.",
                "The error sources were:"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " sample atom content - 2% of systematic error."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " gamma flux - 10% of the systematic uncertain-",
                " ty in the photopeak  efficiency  determination  plus",
                " 1.5 to 3% of statistical error;"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " photofission events - 3.1%  of the systematic",
                " error in the calibration for fission counting plus 2",
                " to 5% of the statistical uncertainty;"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " photoneutron  events  - 1%  of the systematic",
                " error in the calibration for neutron counting plus 6",
                " to 10% of the statistical uncertainty;",
                " The experimental errors in nu(e) and in the relative",
                " intensity of the gamma-ray lines were  not  included",
                " in any error analys.",
                "These values resulted in a overall  uncertainties  of",
                " about 15% for the final photofission cross sections,",
                " about 20%  for the final total neutron cross  secti-",
                " ons,  and ranged from 20 to 50% for the final photo-",
                " neutron cross sections. M0381 1 54"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photofission  and  photoneutron cross sections of",
                " U-233 have been measured by using monochromatic  and",
                " discrete photons produced by thermal neutron capture",
                " gamma-rays in several targets placed at the core  of",
                " the  IAA-R1 reactor in the energy interval from 5.43",
                " to  9.72  MeV.   The   evaluation   of   the   total",
                " photoabsorption  cross  sections and the parameters:",
                " single  fission  barrier,  relative  fissionability,",
                " fission    probability,   neutron   emission/fission",
                " competition, nuclear temperature are also presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
